-- Share in RBS, Lloyds higher after saying they could re-locate
-- 
-- Thu Sep 11, 2014 03:04AM EDT
-- None



LONDON, Sept 11 (Reuters) - Shares in Royal Bank of Scotland opened up 2 percent and Lloyds Banking Group <LLOY.L> shares were up 1.5 pct after the Scottish banks said they would re-locate to London if Scots vote for independence.   (Reporting by Matt Scuffham)  ((matthew.scuffham@thomsonreuters.com; 02075426734; Reuters Messaging: matthew.scuffham.reuters.com@reuters.net))  Keywords: SCOTLAND INDEPENDENCE BANK SHARES

